@Node Edito "Editorial"

Heads up !
 
Before  anything, I wish  you a Happy New Year. I hope that 1997 will
be a very good year for you, with tons of new CD's and good news from
your preferred bands.

This  year, we're waiting for new material from  Machine  Head,  Fear
Factory, Iron Maiden, Metallica ( with the following  of  Load )  and
many more. We will, of course, tell you the  latest news when they'll
be out.

So, Point & Rock begins to  get some  response. Continue in this way.
It seems that most of you are pleased  to read this mag. Many of you,
dear readers, told me to  continue  in  this way. I will ! But I need
more and more support...

In this issue, we will talk a little bit of Guns n' Roses. Things get
special in this band : Slash is out ! We have investigated on the net
to find out more. You will read the results further in this issue.

I was speaking of a  surprise last  edition. I had planned to provide
you a live record of Pearl Jam in Germany, but things went wrong ( my
brother scratched the tape ) so I have nothing to give ya. I have old
records of Metallica and  Aerosmith  at Woodstock II on tapes. If you
are interested, contact me.

We are also Internet connected. So, if you have access to this media,
you can  contact  me at Thunus.Raphael@ping.be to receive a vote form
or to send me your votes, comments...

The  Vote  Form design has been  a little  bit  improved due  to  the
talented ASCII  dude aC!d  from Doggystyle. Thanx to him... Well done
mate !

Well, I'm leaving here, have a nice reading and Happy New Year...



                                         Raphaël ^ Mister No/aßS

@Endnode

