@Node Article "Slash leaves Guns N' Roses"

@{"Slash" Link sys:Images/slash.gif/MAIN}

It seems that it's definitely a fact : Slash is actually  out of Guns
N' Roses. We have decided to investigate through  the net to discover
more  informations  about  that  major  news  for the end of 1996. We
suggest  you  to go  on to  the next  web  pages  to read it. We have
managed to summarize the different infos found there.

http://www.students.uiuc.edu/~t-gray/axl.html
http://www.metaverse.com/vibe/sleaze
http://casemix.queensu.ca/marina/garden.html

Here follows a text transcripted from MTV news dated 1 November 1996.
 
" Guitarist  SLASH  has finally  walked out on GUNS N' ROSES after 11 
years. The split  was  apparently by "mutual agreement" with frontman
AXL ROSE. Ironically, last week Slash  admitted  he didn't know if he
had a future in the heavy rock  group. He said, "It's  really hard to
say where that's going to go. I don't even know if I'm going to be in
the band or not. Right now I'm just  going  through  a trial  period.
A lot has gone on between me and Axl. He and  I have  only had dinner
twice where we've  managed to get to  the point where we were civil."
Gun N' Roses, who haven't released an album  for four years, will now
be looking for a replacement  for Slash. But they  insist  they won't
be inviting former axe man  IZZY STRADLIN  back into the fold. Slash,
meanwhile, will carry on working with  the  SLASH'S SNAKEPIT group he
formed two years ago while Guns 'N' Roses took a lengthy hiatus. "



THE Fax ( sent to MTV )

LIVE!!!!  From "Burning Hills", California...

Due  to  overwhelming  enthusiasm, and  that "DIVE  IN  AND  FIND THE
MONKEY" attitude.... 

#1. There will NOT be a Guns N' Roses tour.
#2. There will NOT be an official Guns N' Roses web site.
#3. There will NOT be any NEW Guns N' Roses videos.
#4. There will NOT be any new Guns N' Roses involved merhandise.
#5. There will NOT be a Guns N' Roses Fan Club.
#6. There will be a new Guns N' Roses 12 songs minimum recording with
    three original "B" sides.
    NOTE:  If all goes well this will be immediately repeated.
#7. However*******Slash will not be involved in any new Guns N' Roses 
    endeavors, as  far  has  not been musically involved with Guns N'
    Roses since April 1994 with the exception of  a BRIEF feel period
    with Zakk Wylde and a 2  week initial  period with  Guns N' Roses
    in the  late fall  of '95.  He (Slash)  has  been "OFFICIALLY and
    LEGALLY"  outside of the Guns N' Roses Partnership since December
    31, 1995.


		Nothing here is Subject To Change
		Without A PERMANENT SUSPENSION
		Of the "Pseudo Studio Musician Work Ethic"
				SINCERELY,
				W. AXL ROSE (signed)
				W. Axl Rose

2 hypothesis are now available : Slash left  GNR  alone or  Slash has
been kicked away by the two other original members of  the band : Axl
and Duff. We can't say wich one is the truth.

We sure understand the position of Slash : he has been  bored  to see
his ideas continually rejected by Axl ( we've read that  the material
of "It's 5 O'Clock Somewhere" was  destined  to  the new album of the
gunners ). That's why he build up the Snakepit, waiting Axl to  be in
better mood. But Axl has been bored to see Slash out  of Guns... This
applies too to Duff and Matt : Axl threaten them to be kicked away if
they don't stop working  with Neurotic  Outsiders. Axl the Tyrant !!!

From  here, why don't think about an Axl Only Guns n' Roses  band ???
He said that he owns the rights of the name so he  can  edit an album
with every musician he wants...

We're now waiting for more informations  about  that subject. We will
tell you them when we'll get it. One thing is sure, Axl wants to edit
a new album for GNR. Let's hope it will be so  good than Appetite for
Destruction ( I've some doubts... )

@Endnode


