###############
# Final Words #
###############

@Node Final "Final Words"

Finally, I made it ! I'm on my way now : the third  edition  is over.
It has been a pleasure to  be  with  you  once again. I would like to
encourage you to continue to support me. I begin  to get some answers
and it's very nice. The Load's Lyrics seem to pleased some of you, so
I'll do it again with other bands. 

On  the  other  side, someone  told  me  that  P&R was  a  little bit
commercial sometimes. He was speaking  about  the charts, complaining
about seeing  Bon  Jovi  and  Garbage in it... I must tell that I use
the charts of 2 Hard  Rock  magazines  to  build mine ( and also with
YOURS ). The two bands named above were classed in  those mags, so it
was  reflected in mine... If you want  to  see  a  more "underground"
chart, then vote ! The 25 best albums will be in the mag.

I also hope that the improvements done with the graphics pleased you.
Tell me what do you think about the photos. I know  there were only 2
pictures in this mag but I hope to give you  more  next time. All you
need is working datatypes for jpeg and gif ( the  2  usual formats of
pics on the net ).

If you have interesting  links  to  web pages, E-mail me the address.
I'm planning to edit a list of Web pages for  every band we can find.
Help me in this adventure !

So, it's really the end now, I will  see  you  in  two months for the
next edition : number 4 of Point & Rock !

--- I want Rock and Roll all nite, and party every day --- Kiss


                                Yours, 
                                Mister No ^ aßS


@endnode

####################
# Albums to listen #
####################

@Node Albums "Albums to listen"

@{b}@{"Anathema" Link AnaInfo} : Eternity@{ub}

This month I will talk you about the new album  of Anathema. First of
all, I  could  tell  you  to  not  listen  this album if you are in a
depressive state of mind : you  could  easily  pull  a bullet in your
head !!!

However, this album is fantastic. The first audition is disappointing
because you must listen it 2 or 3 times again to discover what it has
to give. 

After a splendid intro where  the  guitars  are  sadly accompanying a
piano, you will enter in  a world full of  atmospheres  created  with
keyboards. Everything is very dark and sad. The bass  lines are good.
It's an excellent piece of doom work !

One single song escape from this lot : it's a  reprise  of  a song of
David Gilmour and Roy Harper.

So, my final quote for this piece of musical  depression is 9/10. You
know what you have to do if you like doom ( if it's  not already done
of course ).

@endnode


####################
# News and rumours #
####################

@Node News "News and rumours"

One thing we could say about  this edition's news and rumours is that
there  is  a lot  of new  albums  ready  to  be  heard and the actual
tendency is to reform original bands... Read what we mean !

@{b}Aerosmith@{ub}

The new album of Aerosmith is planned to be out on the 18th of march.

@{b}Alice Cooper@{ub}

Alice  Cooper  has  a  new live album ready to invade your CD reader.
It's called " A Fistful Of Alice " and it'll be out in january.

@{b}Faith No More@{ub}

Faith No More are still alive and plan to have a new record in spring
1997. They have also a new guitarist : John Hudson.

@{b}Foo Fighters@{ub}

The  Foo  Fighters  are  in  studio to give a little brother to their
first album... Expected in march.

@{b}Mötley Crüe@{ub}

After Kiss, after Van  Halen, after WASP, the  new one in the race of
reforming  is  Mötley  Crüe : Vince  Neil  could  rejoin  the Crüe...
Unbelievable !!! We're waiting for an unprobable reformation of Black
Sabbath ! ( Joke... )

@{b}Nuno Bettencourt@{ub}

The ex-guitarist of Extreme ( dead now ) has finished  his first solo
album called " Schizophonic ". It's  due  to  be  out  on the 11th of
february.

@{"Ozzy" Link OzzyInfo}

A best of Ozzy should be out soon.

@{b}Rainbow@{ub}

We have read that Joe  Lynn  Turner  could come back in Rainbow... No
comment !

@{b}Silverchair@{ub}

Their new album is planned  for  the  4th of february  and  is called
" Freakshow ".

@{b}Sonic Youth@{ub}

The new album of the noisy americans is  called " Dirty Windows " and
sould be out soon.

@{b}The Cult@{ub}

The Cult is back but without Ian Astbury... No comment !


@endnode



